The claim to the "World's Largest Orchestra" belongs to Venezuela, following a Guinness World Record attempt featuring thousands of musicians from across the country, and one man on a mission. Andrés David Ascanio is an accomplished trumpet player and music conductor, schooled in a unique Venezuelan style of teaching music. Yet, for Andrés, his unflinching faith in music is more than uniting the country through music. Mary Triny Mena tells us more from Caracas.